fields.title: Fundraise for Code Platoon
fields.event_venue_address: Millennium Park, 201 E Randolph St, Chicago, Illinois 60602, United States
fields.description: Join us for a heartwarming day at the park as we rally support for our veterans' transition to civilian life through education and empowerment. Our fundraiser aims to raise funds for our esteemed coding bootcamp tailored for active military, veterans, and military spouses!

fields.title: Farmers Market to Help Farmers
fields.event_venue_address: Bailey's Farmers Market, 4301 N Davis Hwy, Pensacola, Florida 32503, United States
fields.description: Join us for a rewarding day of community engagement at our local farmers market! As a volunteer, you'll play a vital role in supporting local farmers, artisans, and small businesses while promoting healthy living and sustainable practices. Tasks may include setting up vendor booths, assisting customers, managing traffic flow, and helping with event logistics. Whether you're passionate about agriculture, food sustainability, or simply love connecting with people, this volunteer opportunity offers a fun and fulfilling way to make a difference in our community. Come be a part of the vibrant atmosphere, enjoy fresh produce, and contribute to the success of our beloved farmers market!

fields.title: Glow Run
fields.event_venue_address: River Walk, San Antonio, Texas 78205, United States
fields.description: We are organizing a nighttime run where participants wear glow-in-the-dark accessories. The route will be lined with glowing markers and lights, and we are also hosting a dance party with glow sticks at the finish line. Great fun for everyone!

fields.title: Hero Run Fundraiser for Teachers
fields.event_venue_address: Central Park, New York City, New York, United States
fields.description: Come join us as we run through the heart of the city to increase visibility for teacher's appreciation week!  Plus, dressing up as your favorite heroes will be super fun! We are raising money for teacher's supplies and classroom supplies

fields.title: Taste of the Town - A Culinary Journey for Charity
fields.event_venue_address: Washington, District of Columbia, United States
fields.description: This event invites local restaurants and chefs to set up booths in the iconic Union Station, where they can showcase their best dishes. Participants purchase tickets that allow them to sample different offerings, turning a taste of the city into a journey of flavors. The grand architecture of Union Station adds a touch of elegance to the event, enhancing the dining experience. Proceeds from ticket sales go to a local food bank or a charity focused on hunger relief.

fields.title: Grill & Chill BBQ Bash - BBQ for a Better Planet
fields.event_venue_address: Zilker Park, Austin, Texas, United States
fields.description: Host a laid-back outdoor barbecue event in Zilker Park, a beloved green space in the heart of Austin. The event features live country music, a range of barbecue vendors from classic Texas brisket to innovative fusion styles, and craft beer tents from local breweries. Attendees buy a pass that gives them access to unlimited tastings. This casual, family-friendly environment is perfect for a sunny day of fun, food, and philanthropy, supporting environmental sustainability projects.

fields.title: Global Kitchen Gala - Cook for a Cause
fields.description: This virtual event invites participants to a live cooking demonstration featuring chefs from around the world. Each chef prepares a signature dish, teaching attendees how to cook it in real-time via an online platform. Tickets include access to the live sessions, downloadable recipe cards, and an optional ingredient delivery package for those who want the full cooking experience. This culinary journey celebrates global cultures and raises funds for international hunger relief efforts.

fields.title: Bake-Off Bonanza - Rising Dough for Education
fields.description: This event encourages amateur bakers and professionals alike to participate in a virtual baking competition. Contestants submit videos of themselves baking their specialty items, which are then judged by a panel of celebrity chefs during a live-streamed event. Viewers can donate to vote for their favorite entries, with all proceeds going to support local food education programs. The event culminates in an online auction of baked goods made by local celebrity chefs.

fields.title: Concert for a Cause - Notes of Change
fields.event_venue_address: House of Blues, 329 N Dearborn St, Chicago, Illinois 60654, United States
fields.description: This event features a lineup of popular local bands and solo artists performing live at an outdoor venue such as a park or amphitheater. Along with music, the event includes food trucks, a merchandise booth selling items from the performing artists, and a raffle drawing with prizes donated by local businesses. Tickets are sold online and at the gate, with all proceeds going to a local charity supporting arts education in schools.

fields.title: Community Day Out - Fun in the Park for a Cause
fields.event_venue_address: Pike Place Market, 85 Pike St, Seattle, Washington 98101, United States
fields.description: Host a social hangout day at Millennium Park, inviting the community to enjoy a day of fun and relaxation. This event features local bands, picnic areas, and games like giant Jenga or cornhole. Entry is free, but fundraising is driven by sales of food from local vendors, branded merchandise, and optional donations for special activities like face painting or balloon art. It's a family-friendly day aimed at strengthening community ties and supporting local charities.
